      Vacation banking
   =20
 =20

A widespread belief among investment bankers=C2=A0is that you have to work =
100-hour weeks, at least early in your career, to be good at the job. There=
 is a lot to learn, and you need to get it down by heart; you need to demon=
strate total commitment to your bank and its clients; you need to respond t=
o client requests instantly even if it takes all night; you need to absorb =
the culture of banking. This stuff just can=E2=80=99t be done in 40 hours a=
 week. Maybe=C2=A080; maybe you can have a few protected weekends or work-f=
ree vacations. But it=E2=80=99s not a 9-to-5 job.
A lot of people find this belief weird and implausible. =E2=80=9CWhy not hi=
re twice as many people, pay them half as much and let them=C2=A0work 40 ho=
urs a week,=E2=80=9D those people ask. =E2=80=9CNonsense,=E2=80=9D old-scho=
ol investment bankers say, =E2=80=9Cthat wouldn=E2=80=99t work at all, you =
don=E2=80=99t understand anything.=E2=80=9D I am a former investment banker=
 myself, and I tend to=C2=A0think that the bankers make some good points. B=
ut I don=E2=80=99t know. It=E2=80=99s possible that they =E2=80=94=C2=A0we =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0all have blinders on, that we were hazed by our banking expe=
riences and unthinkingly pass on the mistakes that were inflicted on us to =
the next generation. Maybe it would be better to hire more people and work =
them 40 hours a week; maybe they=E2=80=99d be=C2=A0better=C2=A0bankers if t=
hey had more time to think and sleep and socialize. I don=E2=80=99t know. T=
here are not really any controlled experiments.
Until now:

Citigroup has opened its new hub for junior investment bankers in the beach=
side Spanish city of M=C3=A1laga, insisting the move is more than a gimmick=
 as Wall Street lenders battle for young talent amid criticism of burnout i=
n banking.
The US bank selected 27 analysts from more than 3,000 applicants for the tw=
o-year programme, which started on Wednesday. Promising eight-hour days and=
 work-free weekends, it aims to distinguish itself from the punishing seven=
-day working weeks common for young staff in London and New York. =E2=80=A6
However, some rivals have dismissed the idea as a stunt that could ultimate=
ly hamper the careers of those who decide to spend their initial years work=
ing less than half the hours and earning about half the starting salary of =
their peers in Citi=E2=80=99s main offices. ...
=E2=80=9CSometimes banks burn out our analysts, so we want to prove they ca=
n work limited hours and still add value,=E2=80=9D [Citi=E2=80=99s=C2=A0Mar=
=C3=ADa D=C3=ADaz del R=C3=ADo] added. =E2=80=9CWhen they are working on M&=
A deals, maybe we will ask them to work longer, but will compensate them wi=
th more holidays. They will be the fresh ones on live transactions, they wi=
ll have more time to think and be creative.=E2=80=9D

I mean it=E2=80=99s not really a controlled experiment; you had to apply fo=
r M=C3=A1laga, so presumably it selects for people who value lifestyle over=
 commitment, and it=E2=80=99s in M=C3=A1laga =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ca sunn=
y, culture and food-orientated city on Spain=E2=80=99s southern coast that =
is far from the world=E2=80=99s biggest financial hubs=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0rather than London or New York.=C2=A0They should have randomly assign=
ed junior analysts to work either 40-hour weeks on the 30th floor of their =
New York office or 80-hour weeks on the 31st floor. Remove all the confound=
ing variables and see who does a better job.=C2=A0
Still it is a fun experiment. Do you think it=E2=80=99s true that =E2=80=9C=
they will have more time to think and be creative=E2=80=9D? Or do you think=
 that they will be watching the clock and doing the minimum so they can lea=
ve at 5 for culture and food? I mean, I know what Citi thinks:

After two years, those who have performed well will have the opportunity to=
 apply for jobs in New York, London or elsewhere.
=E2=80=9CThere is obviously a question about how many will choose to go int=
o a full-time, mainstream investment banking career,=E2=80=9D said [Citi=E2=
=80=99s co-head of investment banking, Manolo]=C2=A0Falc=C3=B3. =E2=80=9CIf=
 you want to go all the way, you have to move from M=C3=A1laga eventually.=
=E2=80=9D

Well. If in 20 years the M=C3=A1laga alums are the ones running Citi =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0if their extra time to think creatively and soak up culture positi=
oned them to be better bankers
  [5]
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0then I suppose that would change? If the M=C3=A1laga plan i=
s so good, why would you have to move on from it?=C2=A0

