<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Vacation banking</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A widespread belief among investment bankers=
=C2=A0is that you have to work 100-hour weeks, at least early in your caree=
r, to be good at the job. There is a lot to learn, and you need to get it d=
own by heart; you need to demonstrate total commitment to your bank and its=
 clients; you need to respond to client requests instantly even if it takes=
 all night; you need to absorb the culture of banking. This stuff just can=
=E2=80=99t be done in 40 hours a week. Maybe=C2=A080; maybe you can have a =
few protected weekends or work-free vacations. But it=E2=80=99s not a 9-to-=
5 job.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A lot of people find this belief weird and imp=
lausible. =E2=80=9CWhy not hire twice as many people, pay them half as much=
 and let them=C2=A0work 40 hours a week,=E2=80=9D those people ask. =E2=80=
=9CNonsense,=E2=80=9D old-school investment bankers say, =E2=80=9Cthat woul=
dn=E2=80=99t work at all, you don=E2=80=99t understand anything.=E2=80=9D I=
 am a former investment banker myself, and I tend to=C2=A0think that the ba=
nkers make some good points. But I don=E2=80=99t know. It=E2=80=99s possibl=
e that they =E2=80=94=C2=A0we =E2=80=94=C2=A0all have blinders on, that we =
were hazed by our banking experiences and unthinkingly pass on the mistakes=
 that were inflicted on us to the next generation. Maybe it would be better=
 to hire more people and work them 40 hours a week; maybe they=E2=80=99d be=
=C2=A0<em>better=C2=A0</em>bankers if they had more time to think and sleep=
 and socialize. I don=E2=80=99t know. There are not really any controlled e=
xperiments.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29049995.262538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMTE5ZTIyNGIt=
ZjEyNi00YTM0LWI3NzUtZGIwNjY2Yzk3YzMzP3NoYXJlVHlwZT1ub25naWZ0/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB41fb2f74" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Until now</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Citigroup has opened its new hub for junior in=
vestment bankers in the beachside Spanish city of M=C3=A1laga, insisting th=
e move is more than a gimmick as Wall Street lenders battle for young talen=
t amid criticism of burnout in banking.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US bank selected 27 analysts from more tha=
n 3,000 applicants for the two-year programme, which started on Wednesday. =
Promising eight-hour days and work-free weekends, it aims to distinguish it=
self from the punishing seven-day working weeks common for young staff in L=
ondon and New York. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">However, some rivals have dismissed the idea a=
s a stunt that could ultimately hamper the careers of those who decide to s=
pend their initial years working less than half the hours and earning about=
 half the starting salary of their peers in Citi=E2=80=99s main offices. ..=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CSometimes banks burn out our analysts=
, so we want to prove they can work limited hours and still add value,=E2=
=80=9D [Citi=E2=80=99s=C2=A0Mar=C3=ADa D=C3=ADaz del R=C3=ADo] added. =E2=
=80=9CWhen they are working on M&amp;A deals, maybe we will ask them to wor=
k longer, but will compensate them with more holidays. They will be the fre=
sh ones on live transactions, they will have more time to think and be crea=
tive.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean it=E2=80=99s not really a controlled ex=
periment; you had to apply for M=C3=A1laga, so presumably it selects for pe=
ople who value lifestyle over commitment, and it=E2=80=99s in M=C3=A1laga =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ca sunny, culture and food-orientated city on Spain=
=E2=80=99s southern coast that is far from the world=E2=80=99s biggest fina=
ncial hubs=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0rather than London or New York.=C2=A0The=
y should have randomly assigned junior analysts to work either 40-hour week=
s on the 30th floor of their New York office or 80-hour weeks on the 31st f=
loor. Remove all the confounding variables and see who does a better job.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still it is a fun experiment. Do you think it=
=E2=80=99s true that =E2=80=9Cthey will have more time to think and be crea=
tive=E2=80=9D? Or do you think that they will be watching the clock and doi=
ng the minimum so they can leave at 5 for culture and food? I mean, I know =
what Citi thinks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After two years, those who have performed well=
 will have the opportunity to apply for jobs in New York, London or elsewhe=
re.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThere is obviously a question about h=
ow many will choose to go into a full-time, mainstream investment banking c=
areer,=E2=80=9D said [Citi=E2=80=99s co-head of investment banking, Manolo]=
=C2=A0Falc=C3=B3. =E2=80=9CIf you want to go all the way, you have to move =
from M=C3=A1laga eventually.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well. If in 20 years the M=C3=A1laga alums are=
 the ones running Citi =E2=80=94=C2=A0if their extra time to think creative=
ly and soak up culture positioned them to be better bankers<a class=3D"foot=
note-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !importan=
t; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0then I suppose that would change? If the M=C3=A1laga pl=
an is so good, why would you have to move on from it?=C2=A0</p>
