<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes, well, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/29049995.262538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlc=
y90d2l0dGVyLXdoaXN0bGVibG93ZXItaGVhZHMtdG8tY29uZ3Jlc3MtYWhlYWQtb2Ytc2hhcmVo=
b2xkZXItdm90ZS1vbi1lbG9uLW11c2tzLTQ0LWJpbGxpb24tdGFrZW92ZXItYmlkLTExNjYzMDY=
xNDAzP21vZD1ocF9sZWFkX3BvczE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB194b5ad2" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> cl=
early</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter Inc. shareholders approved the $44 bil=
lion takeover that Elon Musk is trying to abandon on the same day that a wh=
istleblower alleged at a hearing on Capitol Hill that the social-media comp=
any misled regulators about security failures. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter shareholders approved the takeover off=
er, with 98.6% of votes cast at a special meeting in favor of the deal, bas=
ed on a preliminary tally of votes, the company said after polling closed T=
uesday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29049995.262538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMTMvY3J5cHRvLXdhbnRzLXNvbWUtc2VjLXJ1bGVzP2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDA5MTQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cD25e58094" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  talked about this yesterday</a>;=C2=A0I said it w=
ould be pretty silly to vote against the deal. And in fact almost no one di=
d. Only about <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2904=
9995.262538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGE=
vMTQxODA5MS8wMDAxMTkzMTI1MjIyNDQyODkvZDQwMzMwNmQ4ay5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cCcfee1e0d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> 60% of Twitter=E2=80=99s shares</a> voted at all,=
 but that was plenty to approve the deal. It is not immediately clear to me=
 whether Elon Musk voted his shares in favor of the merger, as he was oblig=
ated to do under the merger agreement (unless he has terminated the agreeme=
nt (which he says he has (though Twitter says he hasn=E2=80=99t))), but he =
certainly didn=E2=80=99t vote=C2=A0<em>against=C2=A0</em>the merger, and an=
yway it doesn=E2=80=99t matter either way.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, about 4.1 million shares =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0about $173 million worth =E2=80=94=C2=A0voted against the deal. Why? I g=
uess you could tell a couple of=C2=A0stories. One is, you=E2=80=99re a Twit=
ter shareholder because you believe in the long-term value of the company. =
You think that it has a huge opportunity to make a ton of money, and that i=
ts current management has the ability to execute against that opportunity. =
You have built a financial model and it says that Twitter is worth $70 per =
share, based on the discounted value of its expected (by you) future cash f=
lows. So you don=E2=80=99t want to sell to Elon Musk at $54.20; you want to=
 keep your shares in this valuable company. All very possible. Very much a =
minority opinion! But 1.4% of shareholders=C2=A0might think this, sure.<a c=
lass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpare=
nt !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other is, you=E2=80=99re a Twitter shareho=
lder and also have some sort of socially-responsible-investing view. Perhap=
s you have a mandate to pursue the best interests of all stakeholders in th=
e companies you invest in. Perhaps you are an individual investor and you w=
ant to do good with your money. Perhaps you are a diversified index-y inves=
tor and you think a lot about the systemic effects of your investment. In a=
ny case, you evaluate the situation holistically, and you say =E2=80=9Cwell=
, sure, Twitter is worth less than $54.20, but I think it will be bad=C2=A0=
<em>for the world=C2=A0</em>(or for Twitter=E2=80=99s employees, its users,=
 etc.) for Elon Musk to own it, so I am going to vote against the deal.=E2=
=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #000=
000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bot=
tom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color:=
 transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suspect this is even more of a minority opin=
ion.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-8" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: t=
ransparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[8]</span>
</a> We talk a lot around here =E2=80=94=C2=A0lots of people talk a lot=C2=
=A0everywhere =E2=80=94=C2=A0about socially responsible investing and ESG a=
nd stakeholder capitalism and the purpose of corporations. And certainly ba=
ck when Elon Musk said he wanted to buy Twitter, he said he wanted to do it=
 for social and philosophical reasons. You could imagine the shareholder vo=
te being about people=E2=80=99s competing visions for Twitter as a product =
and as a public service. But, nah.=C2=A0Twitter=E2=80=99s board, and its sh=
areholders, have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
9049995.262538/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjItMDUtMDIvdHdpdHRlci1zLWJvYXJkLWdhdmUtdXA_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkxNDIyX01PTkVZU1R=
