ZXJtPTIyMDkxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe9a=
a4255" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">  what the hedge funds are up to</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hedge funds including David Einhorn=E2=80=99s =
Greenlight Capital and Pentwater Capital Management are wagering that Elon =
Musk won=E2=80=99t get his way this time.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk, the world=E2=80=99s richest person and a=
 renowned sparring partner with regulators over securities laws, is trying =
to back out of his agreement to buy Twitter Inc. for $44 billion. Several h=
edge funds have purchased stock, options or bonds -- speculating that Musk =
will lose a trial scheduled to begin Oct. 17 in Delaware Chancery Court. =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The law is clear, Einhorn told investors in a =
letter last month. And =E2=80=9Cif it were anyone other than Musk, we would=
 handicap the odds of the buyer wiggling out of the deal to be much less th=
an 5%,=E2=80=9D he said. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe think that the incentive of the De=
laware Chancery Court, the preeminent and most respected business court in =
the nation, is to actually follow the law and apply it here,=E2=80=9D Einho=
rn wrote.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, that=E2=80=99s fine, and I think I have =
been pretty clear around here that (1) I also think the odds are against Mu=
sk and (2) this is definitely definitely not investment advice, and if you =
are a hedge-fund analyst making the case for buying Twitter and you=E2=80=
=99re showing your boss my columns, knock it off right now. But mostly I wa=
nt to point out that, while some hedge funds are making this bet, it is not=
 exactly the market consensus. Twitter=E2=80=99s stock closed yesterday at =
$41.74. That probably implies better-than-even odds of the deal closing,<a =
class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-10" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpa=
rent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[10]</span>
</a> but not 95%.=C2=A0<em>Some=C2=A0</em>hedge funds are betting that Musk=
 can=E2=80=99t get out of the deal, but the market has some doubts.</p>
